{
  "texts": [
    "Inquisitive logic has important conceptual motivations, but we will not go into them here (see Ciardelli and Roelofsen 2011, Ciardelli et al.",
    "2015, 2013, Roelofsen 2013).",
    "We take the language of inquisitive modal logic to be the language L ′ (Φ, I) from Definition 1.3 that we used for intuitionistic modal logic.",
    "Formulas of the form φ ∨ ○ ψ (written in the cited papers as '?",
    "{φ, ψ}' or 'φ ⩾ ψ') are no longer thought of as declarative disjunctions, but rather as interrogatives."
  ]
}